  "requiredActions": [
    "Residual of prior finding 2: schema-required consumed fields that are absent still default silently (numericFieldOk(undefined) passes, so missing retryCount/escalationCount/humanCorrectionMinutes become 0); wrong-typed provider/model become null; wrong-typed usage.modelIdentity/providerCost count as present; missing artifactId/routingPlanArtifactId accepted. Validate presence and type of every consumed field and count violations as malformed.",
    "Residual of prior finding 3: malformed attempts are excluded from the valid list and never enter the cost loop, so an accepted outcome with one valid and one malformed attempt emits partial cost as complete with relativeCostUnknownAttempts 0. Count each excluded malformed attempt as an unknown relative-cost contribution.",
    "Residual of prior finding 4: evidence.reportHashes are copied into the proposal without verifying the cited reports exist, hash to those values, or embed the selected manifest hash. Accept the cited report artifacts, verify each supplied hash against contents, and verify each report's manifest hash equals the selected manifest hash.",
    "Residual of prior finding 6: the schema permits splits.calibration.split to equal holdout and either boolean for evaluationOnly. Const-bind the discriminators per split and add negative tests.",
    "Residual of prior finding 7: an attempts/routing collection directory escaping containment returns valid [] with malformed 0, silently uncounted. Return a nonzero malformed count and add collection-directory and individual-file symlink tests.",
    "Residual of prior finding 8: the provider/model/capabilityClass key concatenates unconstrained strings with '/' and collides (provider a/b + model c vs provider a + model b/c). Use an unambiguous encoding such as JSON.stringify of the tuple or a structured key, with a delimiter-collision test.",
    "Coverage gaps noted on otherwise-fixed findings: add a test with an accepted outcome missing elapsed time (finding 1) and a malformed-excluded-attempt cost test (finding 3)."
  ],
